---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Architecture — Docs — Essenfont"
  description="How Essenfont is assembled: donor registry, CpMap, Stitcher, Collection::Builder, and the CFF2 + CBDT outline pipeline."
  canonical="/docs/architecture"
>
  <section class="container docs-page">
    <header class="docs-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Docs · IV</p>
      <h1>Architecture</h1>
    </header>

    <p class="lede">
      Essenfont doesn't draw glyphs. It gathers them from canonical
      OFL-licensed donor fonts and stitches the outlines into one
      OpenType Collection.
    </p>

    <h2 id="pipeline">The pipeline</h2>
    <ol class="pipeline-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Donor registry</strong> — <code>sources/manifest.yml</code>
        declares every donor font, its OFL-compatibility class, and the
        codepoint ranges it covers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>CpMap</strong> — <code>Essenfont::CpMap.from_donors</code>
        scans each donor's cmap and builds a per-codepoint assignment
        map. Outline-ineligible donors (CBDT-only color bitmaps) are
        filtered out so they don't pollute the outline map.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Partitioner</strong> — splits the CpMap across named
        subfonts so each one stays under the 65,535-glyph cap. The
        default <code>ByPlane</code> partitioner emits one subfont per
        Unicode plane (BMP, SMP, SIP, TIP, SSP, SPUA-A, SPUA-B) with
        further sub-splits for overflowing planes (CJK-heavy SIP).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Stitcher</strong> — <code>Fontisan::Stitcher</code>
        copies outline glyphs from each donor into the target UFO via
        <code>GlyphCopier</code>. CBDT color bitmap placeholders are
        injected via <code>CbdtPropagator</code> after the outlines so
        they don't overwrite real glyph data (see
        <code>UniqueGlyphName</code> for the name-deconfliction contract).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Compiler</strong> — each subfont UFO compiles to a
        standalone SFNT (TTF for glyf outlines, OTF for CFF2 outlines).
        CBDT/CBLC tables are spliced in via raw-byte propagation
        (BinData round-trips don't preserve CFF2 cleanly).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Collection::Builder</strong> — packs the compiled
        subfonts into a single OpenType Collection file. Tables are
        deduplicated by SHA256 across faces.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Subsets</strong> — per-block WOFF2 subsets are extracted
        from the TTC for the website via <code>fontisan subset</code>.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="donors">Donor registry</h2>
    <p>
      Each donor entry declares its license, its file (TTF/OTF/TTC/WOFF2),
      its sha256, and (optionally) a remap for codepoints the donor
      places at non-canonical positions. The build refuses to use any
      donor outside the OFL-compatible license policy.
    </p>

    <h2 id="cmap">Cmap priority</h2>
    <p>
      When two donors cover the same codepoint, the Stitcher's
      outline-first ordering ensures the real outline glyph wins the
      cmap mapping. CBDT placeholders are added AFTER the outlines so
      their (lower) GID never shadows the outline's (higher) GID.
    </p>

    <h2 id="cbdt">CBDT color bitmaps</h2>
    <p>
      Color emoji comes from <code>NotoColorEmoji.ttf</code>'s CBDT/CBLC
      tables. The Stitcher adds empty placeholder glyphs for every CBDT
      source GID (so the cmap carries the emoji codepoints) and then
      propagates the raw CBDT/CBLC bytes into the compiled font — the
      bitmap data lives in tables, not in glyph outlines.
    </p>

    <h2 id="reproducibility">Reproducibility</h2>
    <p>
      The build is deterministic given the same donor set + manifest.
      Every artifact carries a sha256 in its release metadata; the
      website's coverage.json and the source repo's cp_map.json are
      both committed for audit.
    </p>

    <p class="next">
      Back to: <a href="/docs">Docs index →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .docs-page { max-width: 760px; padding: 3rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
  .docs-head { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377); margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display, Spectral, serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); margin: 0;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 1rem 0; }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display, Spectral, serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  code {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.875em;
    background: var(--ef-surface, #f2efe9);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .pipeline-list {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: stage;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .pipeline-list li {
    counter-increment: stage;
    padding: 0.875rem 0 0.875rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .pipeline-list li::before {
    content: counter(stage, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.875rem;
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377);
  }
  .next {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
  }
</style>
